By 8.45am, queues near the crash stretched about four miles to the north. Traffic monitoring system Inrix said the vehicles involved in the incident had been moved to the hard shoulder. Traffic monitoring system Inrix said: "Low traffic due to accident, now on the hard shoulder on M1 Southbound from J24 A50 (Nottingham South / East Midlands Airport) to J23 A512 Ashby Road East ( Loughborough )." The incident seems to have happened just south of junction 23a southbound. Shortly after 9am, slight delays on the M1 continued while some stationary traffic on the A50 on the approach to the motorway persisted. However, congestion is set to be relieved soon. MORE TO FOLLOW...